cted by Bedouins right in front of his father. They want to sacrifice the handsome youth to the morning star. After many hardships, the old father finds him alive and well, and both are ordained priests by the bishop of Eluse. With this book, a still little-known text of some literary interest is made accessible to a wider public.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Ancient (to 1453).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChristian martyrszRomevBiography. 0aChristian martyrszRomexBiography. 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 0aNilus ‹Ancyranus› / Narrationes de caede monachorum in Monte Sinai. 4aNilus ‹Ancyranus› / Narrationes de caede monachorum in Monte Sinai. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2005z9783110276985oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978359877832240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311093142640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110931426423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110931426/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2005  aZDB-23-DGGb2005  aZDB-23-GCNc2000d2014